{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Deploy π i and collect trajectories D multi ← {(s j, a j, r j, s j+1, a j+1)}.",
    "Q i ← train a Q-function for π i via Monte Carlo policy evaluation on D multi.",
    "Generate single-turn prompts D single ← {x j } where x j is the prompt that π i uses for state s j.",
    "9: until Q i has converged 10: return π i Other methods for performing policy evaluation include SARSA and off-policy Q-evaluation.",
    "SARSA uses temporal differences (TD), which can have lower variance than Monte Carlo, but the downside is that TD-learning in an LLM setting is expensive and potentially unstable (Hong et al., 2024)."
  ],
